recommended for The crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root intiation : 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage : 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage : 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage : 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

recommended for The crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root intiation : 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage : 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage : 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage : 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

III- Active tillering stage : 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage : 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage : 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

Recommended for the crop requires 4 - 6 irrigations depending on the soil type and rainfall. Wheat crop requires minimum of 5 irrigations at the following critical stages.
I – Immediately after sowing
II – Crown root initiation: 15-20 DAS 
III- Active tillering stage: 35-40 DAS
IV- Flowering stage: 50-55 DAS
V- Grain filling stage: 70-75 DAS
Crown root initiation and flowering are the most critical stages. Water stagnation should be voided at the time of germination.

KCCAns: After 45 days irrigation is stopped and jute bags are removed. After removing the brood, the top manure dries up and the earthworms go into humidity below. Thus, the entire compost separates from the stitches in 3-4 times and the earthworms are left in the last In the stitches in 2 months, the number of earthworms inserted doubles, keep in mind that do not use gantry, spade or cranberries to remove manure from hand. The manure extracted from the strains are dried and filtered in shade and stored in a shady place. The quantity of Vermi compost requires 100 grams, one kilogram of one year plants and 6-8 quintals per acre in the crop. Method for Preperation of bordex pest 
1. Dissolve one kilogram of copper sulphate in 5 liter of water in plastic bucket.
2. Dissolve one kilogram of quick lime in 5 liter of water seperately in plastic bucket.
3. Both solution are mixed in one bucket same time.
4. If the prepare mixture is in acidic range, it can be brought to neutral or near alkaline condition by adding some more lime solution into the mixture. 
5. To test the neutrality of the mixture, dip a well polished knife or a sickle in the mixture for few minutes. If reddish deposit appears on the knife/sickle, it indicates the acidic nature of the mixture.

KCCAns:
WEED MANAGEMENT
Pre emergence application of Pendimethalin @ 3.3 litres per hectare under irrigated condition or 2.5 litres per hectare under rainfed condition on 3 days after sowing using Backpack/ Knapsack/Rocker sprayer fitted with flat fan nozzle using 500 litres of water for spraying one ha. After this, one hand weeding on 30th days after sowing gives weed free environment throughout the crop period (or) EPOE application of quizalofop ethyl @ 50 g ai/ha-1 and imazethapyr @ 50 g ai ha-1 on 15 – 20 DAS.
If herbicide is not applied give two hand weedings on 15 and 30 days after sowing.

It is planted late in the rainy season around August-September and harvested in the next May.



Two months old crop


Field view

Manuring
The crop is mainly grown on residual fertility. Hence, no manure or fertilizers are recommended.

After cultivation
Hand weeding is generally done at 30 days of sowing to control the weeds.

 Plant protection
 Leaf blight and die back- Diethane M 45(0.3%)
Damping off and seedling rot- Trichoderma viride (2 kg/ha) and Pseudomonas flurescens (2kg/ha)

Harvest
The maturity of the crop is judged by the drying of the leaves and berries turning red. The crop is ready for harvest in 150-170 days after sowing, starting from January upto march. The entire plant is uprooted and roots are separated by cutting the stem 1-2cm above the crown.


Maturity stage


Fresh fruits

Post harvest practices
The roots are transversely cut into smaller pieces of 7-10 cm to facilitate drying. The berries are harvested separately, dried and threshed to remove the seeds.



Freshly harvested roots


Washing the roots



Dried roots


Dried seeds

 Grading of roots
The dried roots are beaten with a club to remove adhering soil and to break off thin, brittle, lateral rootlets. Lateral branches, root crown and stem remains are carefully trimmed with a knife. Root pieces are then sorted out into following grades.

1) A grade
Root pieces up to 7 cm in length, 1-1.5 cm in diameter, solid cylindrical with smooth external surface and pure white from inside.

2) B grade
Root pieces up to 5 cm in length, 1 cm or less in diameter, solid, brittle and white from inside.

3) C grade
Solid root pieces up to 3-4 cm in length, 1 cm or less in diameter.

4) D grade
Small root pieces, semisolid or hollow, very thin, yellowish inside and < 1 cm in diameter.
of late farmers are grading the roots into 7 or more grades.

Yield: The crop produces 400-1200 kg/ha dried roots and 200-500 kg seeds/ha.

Preparation of white muesli farm: White muesli is a 8-9 month old crop which is dug in February-March after planting in monsoon. Mix the dung roe compost at the rate of 250 quintals per hectare during the last plowing field.
Seed Treatment and Planting: The business of white muesli is done from cultivating roots. For sowing 1 hectare, 6-10 quintals of fleshy roots are needed.
The muesli is planted in the rainy season. Regular rain does not require irrigation. Give an irrigation in the irregular monsoon in 10-12 days. After October, light irrigation should continue on 20-21 days. Keep moisture in the cultivation till the powdered mustard.
